<A NAME="top"><H1>NC Fresco Online Help</H1></A>
<P>Welcome to NC Fresco help.  This document contains information about the following topics:

<P><A HREF="#intro">Introduction</A>:  Provides a brief overview of the WWW and the browser.
<P><A HREF="#Procedures">Procedures</A>:   Describes how to navigate to URLs, use the Favorites List, search for text, and print.
<P><A HREF="#Toolbar">Using the Toolbar</A>:  Describes the browser toolbar functions.
<P><A HREF="#Keyboard">Using the Keyboard</A>:  Describes the browser keyboard shortcuts.
<P><A HREF="#Messages">Understanding Browser Messages</A>:  Describes the browser error messages.
<P><A HREF="#Glossary">Glossary</A>:  Describes terms and acronyms used throughout the Browser Help.
<P><A HREF="ncfrescointernal:cancel">Return to Browser</A>: Closes this help page and returns you to the Browser.

<P><H2><A NAME="intro">Introduction</A></H2>
The World Wide Web (WWW) gives you easy access to information and resources on the Internet.  In addition to plain text, the WWW brings images, sound files, and video clips to your network computer.  All of this Web information is physically stored as pages on computers around the world. The address for each page of information is called a Uniform Resource Locator (URL). WWW pages are created using HyperText Mark-up Language (HTML).</P>

<P>Each HTML page can have hypertext links to other destinations such as HTML documents or URLs.  When a hypertext link is active, the text is usually highlighted (underlined and appears a different color than surrounding body text).  Clicking on the highlighted text takes you to the destination page or URL.</P>

<P>The Browser enables you to view the information available on the WWW.  In addition to being a Web browser, the Browser supports the following features:</P><P>
<UL><LI><B>Images </B> including GIF (87 and 89 with interlace, transparency, and animation), JPEG, Progressive JPEG, PNG, and Sprite.
<LI><B>Sound </B> including MS WAV, AIFF, .VOC, Psion, Amiga 8SVX, and AU/SND.
<LI><B>General HTML3.2,</B> except FONT FACE and FONT COLOR tags.
<LI><B>Forms - HTML2.0</B>
<LI><B>Tables</B>
<LI><B>Magic Cookies</B>
</UL><BR>

